{"type":"item.completed","item":{"id":"item_18","type":"command_execution","command":"/bin/zsh -lc 'cat -n RULES.md'","aggregated_output":"     1\t# Billing domain rules\n     2\t\n     3\tImplement `computeInvoice(invoice)` in `src/billing.mjs`. All money is in integer MINOR units\n     4\t(e.g. cents). Percentages are in basis points (bps): 1000 bps = 10%.\n     5\t\n     6\tInput:\n     7\t```\n     8\t{\n     9\t  lines: [{ qty, unitPriceMinor, category, lineDiscountBps }],\n    10\t  orderDiscountMinor,   // optional, default 0\n    11\t  shippingMinor         // optional, default 0\n    12\t}\n    13\t```\n    14\t`category` is one of `standard` (20% = 2000 bps), `reduced` (5% = 500 bps), `exempt` (0%).\n    15\t\n    16\tReturn `{ subtotal, totalTax, shipping, grandTotal }` (all integer minor units).\n    17\t\n    18\tDomain rules (these are the point of the task ŌĆö get them exactly right):\n    19\t\n    20\t1. **Line net** = `qty * unitPriceMinor` minus the line discount. The line discount is\n    21\t   `round(gross * lineDiscountBps / 10000)`.\n    22\t2. **Tax is computed PER LINE and then summed** ŌĆö never by applying the rate to the rounded\n    23\t   subtotal. `lineTax = round(lineNet * categoryRate / 10000)`; `totalTax = sum(lineTax)`.\n    24\t3. **Rounding is banker's rounding (round half to EVEN)**, not half-up. e.g. 2.5 -> 2, 3.5 -> 4.\n    25\t4. **`subtotal`** = sum of line nets (after line discounts, BEFORE the order discount).\n    26\t5. **The order-level discount reduces the subtotal only** ŌĆö it does NOT reduce tax. Apply tax first\n    27\t   (rule 2), then subtract `orderDiscountMinor` from the subtotal portion, floored at 0.\n    28\t6. **Shipping is added after tax and is never taxed.**\n    29\t7. `grandTotal` = `max(0, (subtotal - orderDiscount, floored at 0) + totalTax + shipping)`.\n","exit_code":0,"status":"completed"}}
